Our team is having trouble seeing our LaserCANs on Grapplehook. Our LaserCANs are on a separate CAN loop running through a CANivore but not our Roborio. Do LaserCans have to be on the same CAN loop as your Roborio?

ChocolateFreckle:

Do LaserCans have to be on the same CAN loop as your Roborio?

Yes. As far as I am aware, the only devices supported by the CANivore are CTRE devices like Krakens, CANcoders, Pigeon 2 IMU, etc.

Edit: as @kingc95 pointed out, they have to be the CAN FD devices. Older CTRE devices that only support CAN 2.0 won’t work.

From what I know from my day job, CAN FD is flexible data rate and will vary the baud rate based on usage. Whereas CAN 2.0 is a fixed baud rate, I believe at 1 Mb for FRC.
